otting stories relevant to Kurtosys brand positioning. Strong IT and office-based skills backed up by a real interest and intellectual curiosity will be essential for this vital role. Develop a corporate communication (internal and external) strategy Responsible for drafting internal communication content, defining newsworthy stories, and driving internal campaigns Lead external communications by developing and placing relevant business content on thought leadership and corporate announcements The role will include writing press releases, securing media coverage, spotting stories relevant to the work of the organisation Key focus on identifying and collecting key metrics to measure communication program effectiveness, developing and delivering Internal Comms metric overview. In alignment with the marketing strategies, leverage business and product knowledge to design and produce internal and external communications content. Assist with key events and internal launches of new products, services and concepts, including undertaking market research to support launch activities Ensure consistency of corporate messages in marketing related collateral Establishes criteria and formulates projects Leads and provides strategic direction on multiple projects simultaneously, specifically for events. Interfaces with PR media/journalists as well as third party event vendors and suppliers. Work within team structure and provide leadership in developing and implementing internal/employee and external communications plans for wide range of clients to support business and strategic goals. EXPERIENCE REQUIRED Superior oral and written communications and journalistic skills with ability to build relationships as a trusted advisor with leaders/managers Ability to understand, define, and write newsworthy stories Has a journalistic and PR agency experience A solid grasp of the media network in Europe, and US preferably Understands the media landscape in Europe Ability to handle sensitive/confidential information Ability to build network of sources and thrive in a high paced environment Event management and campaign planning experience Experience managing outside vendors and overseeing the design and production of print materials Conversant in and able to use advanced media and various communication platforms (i.e. Newsweaver, social media, etc) Ability to work in a fast-paced environment. Ability to remain focused, objective, effective and concentrated under pressure Innovative \u2013 ability to propose effective, original solutions. Strong attention to detail \u2013 ensures accuracy of communications. Skilled at planning, project management, time management, communicating, decision-making, presentations and human and organizational relations. Is recognised as a Communications expert within own area/geography and has developed a depth or breadth pf complex functional knowledge in own area. Apply Now South Africa United StatesCanada ArgentinaAustraliaBelgiÃ«BrasilDeutschlandEspaÃ±aFranceIndiaIrelandItaliaMÃ©xicoNederlandÃsterreichPortugalSchweizSouth AfricaSverigeUnited KingdomÐ Ð¾ÑÑÐ¸Ñíêµ­ä¸­å½æ¥æ¬ Â© 2020 SH Inc. | Privacy | TermsÂ |Â Privacy Center"
